How do I recover a locked account?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps to recover a locked account:

**1. Self-Service Recovery Options:**
- Go to the login page and click on **“Forgot Password”** or **“Account Locked”**.
- Enter your registered email address or username.
- Check your email for a recovery code and enter it on the recovery page.
- If you do not receive the email, check your spam folder or request the code again.

**2. Password Reset Steps:**
- After entering the recovery code, you will be prompted to reset your password.
- Choose a strong, unique password that meets security requirements.
- If your account was locked due to multiple failed login attempts, wait 30 minutes before retrying or proceed to contact support for immediate help.

**3. Additional Verification:**
- If two-factor authentication (2FA) is enabled, you may need to verify your identity using your recovery phone number or email.
- A verification code will be sent to your recovery option; enter it to continue unlocking your account.

**4. Escalation Procedures:**
- If you cannot access your recovery options or do not receive the verification code, contact the customer support team.
- Provide proof of identity (such as a government-issued ID or employee badge) for manual unlocking.

**Tips to Prevent Future Lockouts:**
- Keep your recovery information (phone number and secondary email) up to date.
- Enable 2FA for added security.
- Avoid sharing your credentials and be cautious of phishing attempts.

For more details, you can refer to the official guides:
- [Recover Locked Account](https://support.techsecure.com/articles/recover-locked-account)[1]
- [Unlock After Failed Logins](https://support.techsecure.com/articles/unlock-account-failed-logins)[2]

[2]: https://support.techsecure.com/articles/unlock-account-failed-logins "How to Unlock Your Account After Multiple Failed Login Attempts"

Query: How can I enable two-factor authentication?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps to enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):

**1. Access Account Settings:**
- Log in to your account and go to **Settings** or **Security Settings** under your profile menu.
- Locate the **Two-Factor Authentication** option and click **Enable** or **Set Up**.

**2. Choose Your 2FA Method:**
- **Authenticator App:** Select this option to use apps like Google Authenticator or Microsoft Authenticator. Scan the QR code displayed on your screen using the app.
- **SMS Verification:** Enter your mobile number and verify it by entering the code sent to your phone.
- **Email Verification (if available):** Some platforms allow sending codes to your registered email.

**3. Complete Setup:**
- After selecting your method, follow the on-screen instructions to link your device or phone number.
- Test the setup by logging out and logging back in to ensure the 2FA prompt appears.

**4. Backup and Recovery Options:**
- Save the backup codes provided during setup in a secure location. These codes can help you regain access if you lose your 2FA device.
- Some platforms allow adding a backup phone number or email for recovery.

**5. Troubleshooting Tips:**
- Ensure your device time is synchronized for authenticator apps.
- If you lose access to your 2FA method, use backup codes or contact support with proof of identity.

For more details, you can refer to these guides:
- [Enable Two-Factor Authentication](https://support.securezone.com/articles/enable-two-factor-authentication)[1]
- [Step-by-Step Setup Guide](https://support.securezone.com/articles/setup-two-factor-authentication)[2]

[1]: https://support.securezone.com/articles/enable-two-factor-authentication "Enabling Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) on Your Account"
[2]: https://support.securezone.com/articles/setup-two-factor-authentication "Step-by-Step Guide to Setting Up Two-Factor Authentication"

Query: How do I change my username?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps to change your username:

**1. Navigate to Account Settings:**
- Log in to your account and go to the **User Portal**.
- Click on your profile icon (usually in the top-right corner) and select **Account Settings**.

**2. Locate the Username Field:**
- Under **Profile Information**, find the **Username** field.
- Click the **Edit** button next to it.

**3. Enter a New Username:**
- Type your desired username, ensuring it meets these requirements:
  - Between **6 and 20 characters**.
  - No special symbols except underscores.
  - Must be unique and not offensive.
- Click **Save Changes**.

**4. Verification:**
- You may need to verify your identity via email or two-factor authentication before the change is finalized.
- Once confirmed, your username will update across all linked services. Note: Some systems may cache your old username for up to 24 hours.[1]

**Restrictions and Policies:**
- You can change your username **once every 30 days**.
- Usernames are case-insensitive and displayed in lowercase.
- Changing your username does **not** affect your login email or password.[2]

**If the Option is Not Available or Issues Occur:**
- Clear your browser cache and cookies, then try again.
- Ensure your new username complies with the guidelines.
- Check your email for verification requests.
- Disable interfering browser extensions.
- Try from a different device or network.
- If the problem persists, contact support with screenshots and details.[3]

[1]: https://support.techsphere.com/articles/change-username "Changing Your Username in the User Portal"
[2]: https://support.techsphere.com/articles/username-change-policy "Username Change Policy and Restrictions"
[3]: https://support.techsphere.com/articles/troubleshoot-username-change "Troubleshooting Username Change Issues"

Query: What should I do if I suspect unauthorized access to my account?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps you should follow if you suspect unauthorized access to your account:

**1. Immediate Actions:**
- **Log out of all sessions:** If possible, sign out from all devices immediately.
- **Disconnect suspicious devices:** Check your account’s active sessions and remove any unknown devices.

**2. Change Your Password:**
- Go to your account settings and reset your password immediately.
- Use a strong, unique password that includes a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols.
- Avoid reusing old passwords.

**3. Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):**
- Navigate to your security settings and enable 2FA.
- Use an authenticator app or SMS verification for added security.

**4. Review Account Activity:**
- Check your recent login history and activity logs for any unauthorized actions.
- Look for changes in settings, linked accounts, or suspicious transactions.

**5. Secure Linked Accounts:**
- If your account is linked to other services (email, social media, payment platforms), review and secure those as well.

**6. Scan for Malware:**
- Run a full antivirus and anti-malware scan on your devices to ensure they are not compromised.

**7. Report the Incident:**
- Contact your service provider’s support team immediately and report the unauthorized access.
- Provide details such as suspicious login times, IP addresses, and any changes you did not make.

**8. Monitor for Further Issues:**
- Keep an eye on your account and email for any unusual activity or security alerts.
- Consider setting up account alerts for logins and changes.

Query: How do I manage my notification preferences?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps to manage your notification preferences:

**1. Access Notification Settings:**
- Log in to your account and click on your **Profile Icon** (usually in the top-right corner).
- Navigate to **Settings** > **Notifications** or **Preferences**.

**2. Available Notification Options:**
- **Email Notifications:** Enable or disable emails for account activity, promotions, or security alerts.
- **SMS Notifications:** Turn on or off text message alerts for important updates or security codes.
- **Push Notifications:** Manage alerts sent to your mobile app or browser.

**3. Customize Your Preferences:**
- For each category (e.g., Security, Promotions, Updates), toggle the switch to enable or disable notifications.
- Some platforms allow you to set frequency (e.g., real-time, daily summary, weekly digest).

**4. Disable All Notifications (Optional):**
- Scroll to the bottom of the notification settings page and select **Turn Off All Notifications** if you prefer not to receive any alerts.

**5. Save Changes:**
- After making your selections, click **Save** or **Apply Changes** to confirm your preferences.

**6. Verify Settings:**
- Log out and back in or check your email/SMS to ensure the changes have taken effect.

Query: How can I link multiple accounts?
Response:
Here are the detailed steps to link multiple accounts:

**1. Navigate to Account Linking Settings:**
- Log in to your primary account.
- Go to **Settings** > **Account Management** or **Linked Accounts**.
- Look for an option labeled **Link Accounts** or **Connect Another Account**.

**2. Supported Account Types:**
- Commonly supported accounts include:
  - Social media accounts (e.g., Google, Facebook, Twitter)
  - Work or school accounts (e.g., Microsoft 365, G Suite)
  - Other service accounts within the same platform ecosystem.

**3. Start the Linking Process:**
- Click **Add Account** or **Link New Account**.
- Select the type of account you want to link from the list of supported options.

**4. Verification Steps:**
- You will be redirected to the login page of the account you want to link.
- Enter your credentials and grant the necessary permissions for account linking.
- Some services may require two-factor authentication (2FA) for added security.

**5. Confirm and Save:**
- After successful authentication, you will be redirected back to your primary account settings.
- Confirm the linked account appears in the **Linked Accounts** section.

**6. Manage or Unlink Accounts Later:**
- To manage linked accounts, return to **Settings** > **Linked Accounts**.
- Options typically include:
  - **Set Primary Account** for login preference.
  - **Unlink Account** to remove the connection.
- Follow the prompts to confirm any changes.
